English: There are many people at the concert.
Spanish: Hay muchas personas en el concierto.

English: We have been waiting for over an hour.
Spanish: Hemos estado esperando durante más de una hora.

English: I found a ten dollar bill on the street.
Spanish: Encontré un billete de diez dólares en la calle.

English: There are twenty students in my class.
Spanish: Hay veinte estudiantes en mi clase.

English: She counted the coins in her pocket.
Spanish: Contó las monedas en su bolsillo.

English: The train leaves at ten in the morning.
Spanish: El tren sale a las diez de la mañana.

English: I am counting the books on the shelf.
Spanish: Estoy contando los libros en el estante.
